  "local_port": 37392,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I want to activate my old whatsapp but I'm over seas and have the old number?",
  "response": "To activate your old WhatsApp account while you are overseas, you will need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Ensure You Have Access to Your Old Number**: Make sure that you can receive SMS messages or phone calls to your old number. If your old number is still active, you can proceed. If not, you may need to contact your mobile service provider to see if you can temporarily reactivate the number or receive messages through other means.\n\n2. **Install WhatsApp**: If you haven't already, download and install the WhatsApp application from the App Store (iPhone) or Google Play Store (Android).\n\n3. **Open WhatsApp**: Launch the app on your device.\n\n4. **Agree to Terms and Conditions**: Read and accept the terms and conditions.\n\n5. **Enter Your Old Phone Number**: When prompted, enter your old phone number in the format required (including the country code). Make sure you select the correct country code corresponding to your old number.\n\n6. **Receive Verification Code**: Choose the method of verification. You can receive a verification code via SMS or a phone call. If you can\u2019t receive SMS, select the call option to receive the code via a voice call.\n\n7. **Enter the Verification Code**: Once you receive the SMS or the call with the verification code, enter it into the app.\n\n8. **Restore Chat History**: If you have a backup of your chats (and it\u2019s associated with your phone number), you will be prompted to restore it.\n\n9. **Set Up Your Profile**: After verification, set up your profile with your name and profile picture.\n\nIf you're unable to receive the verification code because you don't have access to your old number, you may need to reach out to WhatsApp support for assistance. Keep in mind that WhatsApp has strict policies regarding account recovery, so it\u2019s essential to follow their guidelines.\n\n### Tips\n- If you're using a SIM card from a different country, make sure you have a good signal and that international roaming is enabled if necessary.\n- If you're unable to verify your old number, consider using WhatsApp's support option to see if there's a way to recover your account without the old number.\n\n### Note\nAlways ensure that you are using the latest version of WhatsApp to avoid any potential issues during the activation process.",
